MONITOR CODE CORRECTED BY NNDC
THE GUSTAF WERNER CYCLOTRON AT THE SVEDBERG
LABORATORY, UPPSALA UNIVERSITY, WAS USED.
.THE DATA WERE CORRECTED FOR BACKGROUND AND FOR ACCEP-
TANCE EFFECTS. THE FE-56 DATA WERE CORRECTED FOR THE
FE-54 CONTENT OF THE NATURAL IRON SAMPLE.
THE RECOIL PROTONS WERE DETECTED BY A MAGNETIC
SPECTROGRAPH, EQUIPPED WITH FOUR POSITION-SENSITIVE
DRIFT CHAMBERS AND THREE TRIGGER SCINTILLATORS. THE
PROTON ENERGY AND EMISSION ANGLE WAS DETERMINED BY
RAY-TRACING THROUGH THE MAGNETIC FIELD. THE ENERGY
RESOLUTION OF THE SPECTROMETER WAS 2.8 MEV FWHM IN
THE ANGULAR RANGE 0-15 DEGREES, AND 3.7 MEV FWHM IN
THE ANGULAR RANGE 15-30 DEGREES.
THE ERRORS GIVEN ARE STATISTICAL ONLY. IN
ADDITION, THERE IS A SYSTEMATIC CROSS SECTION SCALE
UNCERTAINTY OF 5 PER-CENT.
THE GUSTAF WERNER CYCLOTRON AT THE SVEDBERG
LABORATORY, UPPSALA UNIVERSITY, WAS USED.
A PROTON BEAM OF 100 MEV IMPINGED ON A 150-200
MG/CM2 THICK LITHIUM TARGET, ENRICHED TO 99.98 PER-
CENT IN 7-LI. THE UNAFFECTED PROTON BEAM WAS BENT BY
A MAGNET INTO A WELL-SHIELDED BEAM DUMP, WHILE THE
NEUTRONS WERE COLLIMATED IN A NARROW CONE AT 0 DEGREES
BY A HEAVY COLLIMATOR SYSTEM, BEFORE ENTERING THE EX-
PERIMENTAL AREA ABOUT 8 M AFTER THE PRODUCTION TARGET.
THE NEUTRON BEAM SPOT AT THE IRRADIATION POSITION HAD
A DIAMETER OF 7 CM. WITH A 5 MICROAMP BEAM, THE NEU-
TRON YIELD AT THAT POSITION WAS ABOUT 1.0E+06 NEUTRONS
PER SEC.
.THE NEUTRONS SHOWED A SEMI-MONOENERGETIC NEUTRON SPEC-
TRUM, WITH A FULL ENERGY PEAK AND A LOW-ENERGY TAIL.
THE LATTER WAS SUPRESSED BY TOF AND UNFOLDING TECH-
NIQUES.
.TWO 135 MG/CM2 THICK TARGET FOILS, ENRICHED TO 99 PER-
CENT IN 54-FE, AND TWO 113 MG/CM2 THICK NATURAL IRON
FOILS, WERE MOUNTED IN A MULTITARGET SYSTEM WITH
MULTIWIRE PROPORTIONAL CHAMBERS BETWEEN THE TARGETS.
IN THIS WAY THE ENERGY LOSS IN THE SUBSEQUENT TARGETS
COULD BE CORRECTED FOR. IN ADDITION, A 50 MG/CM2 CH2
TARGET WAS MONTED IN THE CHAMBER FOR NORMALIZATION
PURPOSES. AT ANGLES LARGER THAN 15 DEGREES, PROTONS
FROM REACTIONS ON CARBON IN THE TARGET CHAMBER FOILS
CAN INTERFERE WITH THE HYDROGEN PEAK IN THE CH2
SPECTRUM, AND A 84 MG/CM2 12-C TARGET WAS USED TO
CORRECT FOR THAT.
.DATA OBTAINED FROM N. OLSSON.
